# Project context

Stack: Next.js 16 · React 19 · TypeScript strict · Tailwind v4 · Shadcn/ui · Prettier · ESLint.
Model: claude-sonnet-4-6 — execute, don't over-think.

## Role

You are an executor. The tasks come from Asana (already broken down). Your job is to implement them cleanly, nothing more.

## Commits (Conventional Commits — mandatory)

```bash
type(scope): short imperative description

# Types: feat | fix | chore | refactor | perf | docs | style | test | ci | revert
# Scope: ui | design-system | seo | a11y | perf | infra | config | deps | auth | api
# Body: explain WHY if non-obvious
# Footer: Closes #<issue>
```

## Branch strategy

- `main` — stable, PR only, all CI must pass
- `dev` — integration, PR only, all CI must pass
- `dev-config` — config changes only, branched from dev
- `feat/<slug>` — one feature at a time, from dev

Never push directly to `main` or `dev`.

## Quality gates (must all pass before PR)

```bash
npm run typecheck   # tsc --noEmit
npm run lint        # eslint
npm run format      # prettier --check
npm run build       # next build
```
